        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is previously generally healthy by available history, with no documented chronic disease or prior hospitalizations. Her parent reports that she has had several cough-and-cold illnesses since beginning day care during the winter, reflecting the evidence that young children in day care may experience frequent upper respiratory symptoms [MEDDIALOG:J06.9:0]. There is no grounded evidence here for asthma, immunodeficiency, or another chronic comorbidity, so none is assigned. The current episode includes congestion, cough, runny nose, low-grade fever, and stomach ache [MEDDIALOG:J06.9:5, SNOMED:J06.9]."
          }
        ]
